# Budget Buddy — Cursor Rules

## Project Overview

A personal budget calendar app called "Budget Buddy". Mobile-first PWA built with Next.js App Router, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui, and Supabase.

## Tech Stack

- Next.js 16 with App Router
- Tailwind CSS v4 (no tailwind.config.ts — configured via CSS variables in app/globals.css)
- shadcn/ui components in components/ui/
- Supabase for auth and database
- TypeScript throughout
- date-fns for date manipulation
- Lucide React for icons

## Supabase Schema

### accounts

- id: uuid (primary key)
- user_id: uuid (references auth.users)
- name: text
- starting_balance: numeric
- created_at: timestamptz

### transactions

- id: uuid (primary key)
- user_id: uuid (references auth.users)
- account_id: uuid (references accounts)
- label: text
- amount: numeric (negative for expenses, positive for income)
- date: date (format: yyyy-MM-dd)
- created_at: timestamptz

### recurring_rules

- id: uuid (primary key)
- user_id: uuid (references auth.users)
- account_id: uuid (references accounts)
- label: text
- amount: numeric (negative for expenses, positive for income)
- frequency: text (weekly | biweekly | monthly | yearly)
- start_date: date (format: yyyy-MM-dd)
- end_date: date (nullable)
- created_at: timestamptz

## Supabase Client Usage

- Browser/client components: import { createClient } from "@/lib/supabase/client"
- Server components: import { createClient } from "@/lib/supabase/server" (always await it)
- Never use the service_role key — only anon key in frontend code
- Always use .eq("user_id", user.id) for RLS — never fetch data without filtering by user

## Architecture Rules

- Server components fetch data — no useEffect for data fetching unless absolutely necessary
- Client components handle interactivity only (forms, UI state, router)
- Pattern: server component fetches data → passes as props to client component
- After mutations, call router.refresh() to re-run server components
- Use lib/supabase/server.ts for all server-side fetches
- Use lib/supabase/client.ts for all client-side mutations

## Design System

- Font: Inter
- Background: #F0F4F8
- Card background: #FFFFFF
- Primary: #4F6BED (indigo-blue)
- Positive amounts: #16A34A (green)
- Negative amounts: #DC2626 (red)
- Text primary: #0F172A
- Text secondary: #64748B
- Text muted: #94A3B8
- Border: #E2E8F0
- Border radius: cards 16px, cells 12px, buttons 8px
- Shadows: 0 1px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.06)
- Tailwind color tokens: bg-background, bg-card, text-foreground, text-muted-foreground, text-primary, border-border

## Component Rules

- Never modify files in components/ui/ — those are shadcn primitives
- Icons: always use lucide-react
- Amount display: always use Math.abs(amount) for display, determine +/- from sign of amount
- Amounts are already signed in the DB (negative = expense) — never store type/category
- Date format for DB: yyyy-MM-dd (use date-fns format())
- Date format for display: use date-fns format() with human-readable patterns

## File Structure

- app/(app)/ — protected app pages (calendar, transactions, add, settings)
- app/login/ — public auth page
- components/ — shared components
- components/ui/ — shadcn primitives (do not edit)
- lib/supabase/ — Supabase client helpers
- lib/projection.ts — balance projection engine
- lib/mock-data.ts — old mock data (ignore, will be removed)

## Key Rules

- Mobile-first always — design for 390px width, scale up for desktop
- Never change layout or styling unless explicitly asked
- Never add categories or type fields — amounts are signed
- Always handle the case where a user has no account yet
- Keep prompts surgical — only change what's asked, nothing else
